<i>one of their seniors visited
the theater rehearsal room.</i>

103
00:06:25,351 --> 00:06:28,755
A line that conveys what is in your hearts

104
00:06:28,821 --> 00:06:30,623
to the audience.

105
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:32,592
{\an8}<i>Kinki Kids member,</i>

106
00:06:32,992 --> 00:06:34,360
{\an8}<i>Koichi Domoto.</i>

107
00:06:36,562 --> 00:06:38,931
<i>He is the chairman of Endless SHOCK,</i>

108
00:06:39,232 --> 00:06:41,601
<i>a stage play that has had
over 1,700 showings.</i>

109
00:06:42,301 --> 00:06:44,203
<i>This theater expert has volunteered</i>

110
00:06:44,270 --> 00:06:46,339
<i>to help with the stage production.</i>

111
00:06:49,876 --> 00:06:52,345
<i>As the two of them
nervously listen to his words,</i>

112
00:06:52,779 --> 00:06:56,682
<i>Domoto suddenly brings up
the Show Time slot.</i>

113
00:06:59,085 --> 00:07:00,119
I don't think so.

114
00:07:00,486 --> 00:07:02,622
Do we really need the Show Time?

115
00:07:03,523 --> 00:07:05,792
Doing that as a form of fan service

116
00:07:06,225 --> 00:07:09,729
is kind of a must for Johnny's theater.

117
00:07:10,329 --> 00:07:12,532
That's how I feel.

118
00:07:12,598 --> 00:07:16,302
I don't think Mr. Johnny would say that.

119
00:07:16,569 --> 00:07:19,672
He told me if the main act is good,
you don't need Show Time.

120
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:24,410
-What do they want to show?
-Right...

121
00:07:24,644 --> 00:07:26,846
-It's about what you want to show.
-Okay.

122
00:07:29,048 --> 00:07:33,386
<i>Will they be able to satisfy
the audience without Show Time?</i>

123
00:07:41,093 --> 00:07:43,029
It's good that you're contemplating.

124
00:07:44,063 --> 00:07:45,665
They care about their fans.

125
00:07:46,699 --> 00:07:48,835
Nothing like Koichi back in the day.

126
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:53,105
<i>What Domoto wanted to relay to them
was the importance of</i>

127
00:07:53,339 --> 00:07:56,175
<i>thinking on their own
and deciding on their own.</i>

128
00:07:59,111 --> 00:08:01,814
<i>In order to stand on their own
as performers,</i>

129
00:08:02,114 --> 00:08:04,183
<i>that is the most important thing.</i>

130
00:08:06,118 --> 00:08:08,054
FOR DREAM BOYS

131
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:09,422
<i>Actually, this time,</i>

132
00:08:09,689 --> 00:08:13,092
<i>there was a performance
that Kishi requested himself.</i>

133
00:08:14,827 --> 00:08:15,928
That's good.

134
00:08:18,598 --> 00:08:21,033
<i>It involved this cube.</i>

135
00:08:21,901 --> 00:08:24,871
<i>Controlling the movements of this cube</i>

136
00:08:25,104 --> 00:08:26,339
<i>is quite hard.</i>

137
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:28,875
It takes a lot of muscle.

138
00:08:28,941 --> 00:08:30,676
-Just do a little at a time.
-Yes.

139
00:08:31,511 --> 00:08:34,013
Bring your hand closer to your face.

140
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:36,916
<i>He loses track of time
and immerses himself in practice.</i>

141
00:08:39,018 --> 00:08:40,486
<i>Sweat drips down his back.</i>

142
00:08:43,389 --> 00:08:44,957
This is no good.

143
00:08:45,024 --> 00:08:46,425
My hands aren't working.

144
00:08:46,492 --> 00:08:48,294
You're probably very tired today.

145
00:08:48,361 --> 00:08:49,562
That's true.

146
00:08:49,629 --> 00:08:52,231
-You have to keep aiming higher.
-Right, higher.

147
00:08:52,298 --> 00:08:54,066
That's the minimum requirement.

148
00:08:54,133 --> 00:08:55,034
-The minimum.
-Yes.

149
00:08:55,101 --> 00:08:56,936
-I'll work on that.
-That's good.

150
00:08:57,136 --> 00:08:58,337
I want to go higher.

151
00:08:58,571 --> 00:09:00,072
-Like this?
-Right.

152
00:09:01,207 --> 00:09:03,209
<i>He doesn't just twirl the cube.</i>

153
00:09:05,278 --> 00:09:07,380
<i>They also use it in the flying routine.</i>

154
00:09:08,781 --> 00:09:11,284
-Oh, no!
-It's okay.

155
00:09:11,517 --> 00:09:14,287
<i>He must support this cube
with just his neck.</i>

156
00:09:14,353 --> 00:09:15,221
Okay.

157
00:09:16,789 --> 00:09:18,758
<i>Just in case the cube falls,</i>

158
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:22,929
<i>they planned to have female performers
below him as insurance.</i>

159
00:09:23,696 --> 00:09:24,530
<i>However...</i>

160
00:09:26,332 --> 00:09:27,767
Can I give you my opinion?

161
00:09:28,167 --> 00:09:30,803
I want him to get through it alone.

162
00:09:31,037 --> 00:09:32,104
Without any help.

163
00:09:32,171 --> 00:09:33,806
-Without help?
-Yes.

164
00:09:33,873 --> 00:09:36,075
-You have to take the risk.
-I agree.

165
00:09:36,142 --> 00:09:37,443
They're not your mothers.

166
00:09:37,810 --> 00:09:40,279
-I can't get any help?
-You have to do it yourself.

167
00:09:40,346 --> 00:09:41,847
You have to. No other way.

168
00:09:42,048 --> 00:09:42,882
I see.

169
00:09:44,951 --> 00:09:48,454
<i>Jinguji was watching over Kishi.</i>

170
00:09:50,723 --> 00:09:52,925
Nishikiori once said that he thought

171
