240
00:13:29,675 --> 00:13:31,210
-<i>Namara</i>?
-<i>Namara</i>.

241
00:13:31,277 --> 00:13:33,746
-Oh, like "<i>namara</i> good."
-Like, "seriously good."

242
00:13:33,813 --> 00:13:36,148
-<i>Osasatta</i>.
-<i>Osasatta</i>?

243
00:13:36,215 --> 00:13:39,351
-Like, "time has <i>osasatta</i>."
-Meaning, "time has flown"?

244
00:13:39,418 --> 00:13:41,086
-Thank you.
-No problem.

245
00:13:41,153 --> 00:13:42,788
-<i>Oshitatta</i>?
-<i>Osasatta</i>.

246
00:13:42,855 --> 00:13:44,156
<i>Osasatta</i>.

247
00:13:44,223 --> 00:13:47,193
-<i>Osasatta</i> and <i>namara</i>. Thank you.
-No problem.

248
00:13:47,860 --> 00:13:49,829
<i>Namara</i>, <i>osatatta</i>.

249
00:13:50,062 --> 00:13:51,430
Was it <i>oshitatta</i>?

250
00:13:52,131 --> 00:13:53,933
<i>Kishi-kun</i>

251
00:13:53,999 --> 00:13:55,267
<i>More, Kishi-kun</i>

252
00:13:56,202 --> 00:13:58,003
<i>Namara</i> be mine.

253
00:13:59,138 --> 00:14:01,173
I <i>namara</i> want to hold you.

254
00:14:05,044 --> 00:14:06,245
<i>With their fans,</i>

255
00:14:06,712 --> 00:14:09,415
<i>they continue on their voyage
on this boat called</i>

256
00:14:09,949 --> 00:14:10,850
<i>King & Prince.</i>

257
00:14:19,124 --> 00:14:21,794
<i>As they rehearse for</i> Dream Boys<i>,</i>

258
00:14:21,861 --> 00:14:25,464
<i>Kishi looks especially happy.</i>

259
00:14:25,998 --> 00:14:28,067
-I bought a guitar.
-Huh?

260
00:14:28,133 --> 00:14:29,468
-I bought a guitar.
-Really?

261
00:14:29,835 --> 00:14:31,036
Did you splurge?

262
00:14:31,303 --> 00:14:33,806
I couldn't help it.

263
00:14:36,008 --> 00:14:39,311
<i>A guitar made by a famous manufacturer.</i>

264
00:14:41,614 --> 00:14:44,183
<i>He is known to be a frugal person,</i>

265
00:14:44,650 --> 00:14:47,987
<i>but he splurged in order to
raise his own morale.</i>

266
00:14:48,821 --> 00:14:52,558
-That's a really nice guitar.
-That's why I have to get better.

267
00:14:52,625 --> 00:14:54,927
-Each player has a unique sound.
-I see.

268
00:15:02,301 --> 00:15:04,303
-That's good.
-Okay.

269
00:15:05,838 --> 00:15:08,274
<i>Their rehearsals are coming to an end,</i>

270
00:15:08,340 --> 00:15:11,677
<i>and today is the scene
that talks about the importance of dreams.</i>

271
00:15:13,212 --> 00:15:15,814
People can't live without dreams.

272
00:15:16,448 --> 00:15:18,250
But dreams don't always come true.

273
00:15:18,350 --> 00:15:20,586
What's important...

274
00:15:20,653 --> 00:15:23,289
<i>Domoto, who's helping
with the production, is there.</i>

275
00:15:23,789 --> 00:15:25,090
Some don't come true.

276
00:15:27,259 --> 00:15:30,529
You became number one
in the harsh world of boxing.

277
00:15:30,596 --> 00:15:32,865
When you say,
"in the harsh world of boxing",

278
00:15:32,932 --> 00:15:34,633
right here,

279
00:15:35,134 --> 00:15:38,137
it doesn't really reach the heart.

280
00:15:38,203 --> 00:15:40,272
Saying "in the harsh world of boxing" here

281
00:15:40,339 --> 00:15:44,310
-creates a world of boxing right there.
-Okay.

282
00:15:44,376 --> 00:15:46,445
If you do that, the listeners empathize

283
00:15:46,512 --> 00:15:48,213
-with the lines better.
-Okay.

284
00:15:51,450 --> 00:15:52,785
That may be better.

285
00:15:53,152 --> 00:15:55,354
<i>At that moment, Kishi...</i>

286
00:15:56,488 --> 00:15:57,957
Then it clicks in my mind

287
00:15:58,023 --> 00:15:59,091
that I don't care.

288
00:15:59,325 --> 00:16:00,759
At that moment,

289
00:16:01,260 --> 00:16:03,662
-can I be like this?
-You can stand. Of course.

290
00:16:05,364 --> 00:16:06,732
I don't care about winning.

291
00:16:06,799 --> 00:16:08,734
<i>"I want to stand and deliver my line."</i>

292
00:16:09,501 --> 00:16:11,303
<i>Kishi proposed his own idea.</i>

293
00:16:13,973 --> 00:16:16,942
You became number one
in the harsh world of boxing.

294
00:16:20,312 --> 00:16:22,081
I don't care about winning.

295
00:16:23,449 --> 00:16:24,616
As long as we can...

296
00:16:26,118 --> 00:16:28,687
use our gloves
to recover our bond that was broken.

297
00:16:30,823 --> 00:16:32,191
That was much better.

298
00:16:32,257 --> 00:16:34,693
-I'll go with that then.
-Perfect.

299
00:16:35,127 --> 00:16:35,995
Let's do that.

300
00:16:38,731 --> 00:16:41,333
<i>Thinking and deciding on his own.</i>

301
00:16:42,568 --> 00:16:44,603
<i>He was able to take one step forward.</i>

302
00:16:45,537 --> 00:16:46,905
Take the net away.

303
00:16:47,740 --> 00:16:49,341
<i>Opening day is nearing.</i>

304
00:16:51,343 --> 00:16:52,678
Don't let go.

305
00:16:56,015 --> 00:16:57,683
IMPERIAL THEATRE

306
00:16:57,750 --> 00:16:59,985
<i>It's opening day for the stage play,</i>

307
00:17:00,252 --> 00:17:01,253
Dream Boys.

308
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:03,455
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

309
00:17:03,522 --> 00:17:05,924
<i>Jinguji looks the same as usual.</i>

310
00:17:07,159 --> 00:17:09,061
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

311
00:17:09,128 --> 00:17:10,629
<i>On the other hand, Kishi...</i>

312
00:17:10,829 --> 00:17:12,965
-Your throat?
-What?

313
00:17:13,399 --> 00:17:14,500
My throat's sensitive.

314
00:17:14,967 --> 00:17:16,035
I see.

315
00:17:17,336 --> 00:17:20,072
<i>It's rare to see him with a sore throat.</i>

316
00:17:20,806 --> 00:17:22,241
Good morning.

317
00:17:24,009 --> 00:17:27,212
<i>He was holding an inhaler
to care for his throat.</i>

318
00:17:27,279 --> 00:17:30,149
Stage rehearsal will begin in ten minutes.

319
00:17:30,215 --> 00:17:32,084
This is seriously bad.

320
00:17:34,486 --> 00:17:36,055
Good morning.

321
00:17:36,121 --> 00:17:37,356
<i>Despite that,</i>

322
00:17:37,423 --> 00:17:39,425
<i>he begins the final check.</i>

323
00:17:42,294 --> 00:17:43,962
I had a fever the other day,

324
00:17:44,029 --> 00:17:46,865
-and my throat never recovered.
-I see.

325
00:17:47,599 --> 00:17:49,501
It's so raspy.

326
00:17:50,102 --> 00:17:51,270
Sorry.

327
00:17:51,837 --> 00:17:53,338
<i>That wasn't all.</i>

328
00:17:55,107 --> 00:17:57,443
Can we make it colored?

329
00:17:58,377 --> 00:18:01,380
<i>He suddenly started feeling pain
in his left arm.</i>

330
00:18:03,482 --> 00:18:04,683
TEN MINUTES UNTIL SHOWTIME

331
00:18:04,783 --> 00:18:05,617
<i>Still...</i>

332
00:18:05,684 --> 00:18:06,752
YUTA JINGUJI, YUTA KISHI

333
00:18:09,855 --> 00:18:12,624
<i>No matter what his condition is,
he will stand on stage.</i>

334
00:18:14,927 --> 00:18:16,628
<i>Because that's what he was taught</i>

335
00:18:17,029 --> 00:18:19,398
<i>by the person he holds dear
and his seniors.</i>

336
00:18:21,467 --> 00:18:24,503
-Break a leg.
-Excuse me.

337
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:26,105
<i>The stage play,</i>

338
00:18:26,672 --> 00:18:29,808
Dream Boys<i>,
is about to raise the curtains.</i>

339
00:18:33,378 --> 00:18:34,613
<i>The time has come.</i>

340
00:19:00,105 --> 00:19:04,409
<i>They both went down to 55 kg
and built up their bodies.</i>

341
00:19:11,049 --> 00:19:12,184
<i>As he promised,</i>

342
00:19:12,417 --> 00:19:14,153
<i>he did the cube by himself.</i>

343
00:19:29,234 --> 00:19:32,371
<i>The guitar which he never put down...</i>

344
00:19:46,051 --> 00:19:48,387
<i>The characters they've each built up...</i>

345
00:19:50,956 --> 00:19:54,393
You became number one
in the harsh world of boxing.

346
00:19:56,061 --> 00:19:58,163
I don't care about winning.

347
00:19:59,431 --> 00:20:01,133
As long as we can use our gloves

348
00:20:01,733 --> 00:20:04,203
to recover our bond that was broken.

349
00:20:05,904 --> 00:20:06,772
Look...

350
00:20:07,873 --> 00:20:10,142
it's important to never give up.

351
00:20:10,909 --> 00:20:12,077
No matter what happens,

352
00:20:12,144 --> 00:20:13,979
you can never give up.

353
00:20:15,047 --> 00:20:17,316
You want to become the champion, right?

354
00:20:21,386 --> 00:20:22,788
<i>And the finale...</i>

355
00:20:23,522 --> 00:20:25,724
<i>They both decided to do the Show Time.</i>

356
00:20:26,425 --> 00:20:28,594
<i>They finished the show with a performance</i>

357
00:20:28,860 --> 00:20:30,462
<i>that lured in the audience.</i>

358
00:20:33,198 --> 00:20:36,034
-Thank you for coming today.
-Let's meet again.

359
00:20:36,101 --> 00:20:37,102
Thank you.

360
00:20:37,970 --> 00:20:40,272
Thank you.

361
00:20:41,873 --> 00:20:43,575
{\an8}It was fun.

362
00:20:43,642 --> 00:20:46,311
{\an8}Some scenes gave me goosebumps
as I was acting.

363
00:20:46,745 --> 00:20:49,615
{\an8}It was an amazing experience.

364
00:20:51,516 --> 00:20:52,651
{\an8}<i>And Kishi...</i>

365
00:20:53,418 --> 00:20:54,319
{\an8}Thank you.

366
00:20:54,786 --> 00:20:57,389
{\an8}I'm sure Mr. Johnny was watching.

367
00:20:57,456 --> 00:21:02,127
{\an8}I did everything I could to perform
in a way that would get his approval.

368
00:21:02,427 --> 00:21:05,297
{\an8}I think I was able to perform
with my head held high.

369
00:21:05,831 --> 00:21:07,399
I'll work even harder.

370
00:21:07,866 --> 00:21:09,234
-There's still more.
-Yes.

371
00:21:09,301 --> 00:21:11,003
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

372
00:21:11,069 --> 00:21:12,371
Good work.

373
00:21:14,740 --> 00:21:15,607
<i>That spirit...</i>

374
00:21:17,376 --> 00:21:19,311
{\an8}<i>is passed on to them next.</i>

375
00:21:20,345 --> 00:21:24,116
I do feel like
I don't want to lose to them.

376
00:21:25,884 --> 00:21:28,220
<i>These three will guide the large boat</i>

377
00:21:28,820 --> 00:21:30,255
<i>and depart.</i>

378
00:21:31,356 --> 00:21:32,491
{\an8}TOMOYUKI YARA (36)

379
00:21:32,557 --> 00:21:34,393
{\an8}<i>Next time, it's Tomoyuki Yara.</i>

380
00:21:37,629 --> 00:21:39,898
<i>As one of Johnny's best dancers,</i>

381
00:21:39,965 --> 00:21:42,601
<i>what is this lone performer
going up against?</i>

382
00:21:44,202 --> 00:21:47,372
I don't want Johnny's members
to be looked down on.

383
00:21:48,407 --> 00:21:50,208
{\an8}He is the one-and-only member

384
00:21:50,275 --> 00:21:52,711
{\an8}who specializes in dancing, I believe.

385
00:21:54,379 --> 00:21:56,615
<i>In his 25th year as a Johnny's member,</i>

386
00:21:56,682 --> 00:21:58,116
<i>what is his resolve?</i>

387
00:21:58,950 --> 00:22:00,886
{\an8}He spends all of his time

388
00:22:00,952 --> 00:22:06,325
{\an8}trying to perfect whatever he does,
and I fell in love with his perseverance.

389
00:22:07,125 --> 00:22:10,262
<i>He aims for the biggest stage
in the world.</i>

390
00:22:10,796 --> 00:22:13,265
If you take away dance,
I will have nothing left.

391
00:22:14,299 --> 00:22:15,934
Subtitle translation by Kiko Morita

